Housing Finance, Development Bank in Joint Venture, Nation Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-02-23T07:41:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/housing-finance-development-bank-in-joint-venture-nation-says.html
Housing Finance Ltd., Kenya’s only
publicly traded mortgage company, agreed with East African
Development Bank to jointly finance housing projects, the  Daily
Nation  reported, citing Managing Director Frank Ireri.  The agreement involves building real estate projects
between 500 million shillings ($6.1 million) and 1.5 billion
shillings to plug a housing shortfall in the region, the
Nairobi-based newspaper reported today.  The Kampala-based  East African Development Bank  is owned by
member states Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania and Rwanda. Other
shareholders include, Nairobi-based  Commercial Bank of Africa ,  Barclays Plc  and  Standard Chartered Plc , both in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 